SAFETY AND ENVIRONMENTAL POLICY:

At SSI Technologies, Inc., quality and environmental management means surpassing our customer's expectations for high quality performance, on-time delivery and value while maintaining a safe and healthy environment for our employees as well as our community by diligent prevention of pollution and waste.  Our commitment to customer satisfaction is driven by accomplishing our objectives which include regulatory and customer requirements, continuously improving and the ongoing development of all team members including suppliers and contractors.

FACILITY DESCRIPTION AND REGULATED SUBSTANCES HANDLED:

SSI-Sintered Specialties is the world's largest stainless steel powder metal components manufacturing facility. We specialize in high-temperature sintering of stainless steel, soft magnetic alloy, tool steel, sinter-hardening alloy, and custom powder metal parts. We are unique in the Powder Metal industry with our ability to offer four powder metal process technologies. We serve a diverse range of applications in diverse industries - Automotive, Industrial, Medical, and Ordnance.

The facility is located on a nominal 5 acre site, with paved shipping and receiving areas. The major structures and their designated functions are: 
Receiving Area w/ docks; 
Furnace Room;
Warehouse; 
Shipping Area w/ docks;
Maintenance Room;
Office areas.
Bulk hydrogen storage tanks (2) and liquid nitrogen storage tank (1) located outdoors.

Hydrogen is utilized at SSI Technologies to manufacture metal components by high-temperature sintering. During sintering, compacted metal powders are bonded together by heating at a temperature close to the melting point of the major constituent. 

GENERAL ACCIDENT RELEASE PREVENTION PROGRAM:

The facility has implemented a Process Safety Management program for its hydrogen sintering process operation and maintenance. The PSM Program has been incorporated as both policy, and most importantly, procedure in everyday operations
